<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h1 id="Introduction">Introduction<a class="anchor-link" href="#Introduction"> </a></h1>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>Recently, I submitted a solution to to the <a href="https://www.classiq.io/competition/state-preparation">state preparation problem</a> of the Classiq coding competition. The goal was to prepare a lognormal distribution (with $\mu=0,\sigma=0.1$) using no more than 10 qubits and within $0.01$ L2 accuracy. Crucially, the problem allowed to use any discretization when mapping from the wavefunction to the lognormal probability density. I did not have any good idea about how to solve the problem in a scalable way, but was curious how far one can go by a direct optimization of low-depth circuits jointly with the discretization intervals. To my surprise, depth 1 circuits on 10 (and in fact 9) qubits are already sufficient to achieve the target accuracy. I believe this solution would be eligible for a prize, but I submitted it later than other participants.</p>
<p>What follows is the notebook I submitted as a solution. It was intended for referees of the competition, who needed no introduction to the problem. In the end, I do not think this solution is particularly illuminating, so I will not try to turn it into a comprehensible blog post. But I also see no harm publishing it, so here we go.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">

<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Approach">Approach<a class="anchor-link" href="#Approach"> </a></h2>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>I used fairly straightforward numerical optimization. I was interested if the target lognormal distribution can be approximated by small-depth circuits optimized directly. In other words, I minimized numerically the L2 error as a function of angles in the circuit and discretization intervals.</p>
<p>To my surprise, 9 and 10 qubits circuits with the smallest depth possible (containing only single-qubit gates) are able to give a good enough approximation below the threshold error. The freedom to adjust discretization seems crucial for low-depth circuits.</p>
<p>I also looked how well can one approximate the target distribution for a given number of qubits, assuming that the probability density can take any shape. This corresponds to the maximally expressive circuit, where all $2^n$ amplitudes can be controlled precisely. Of course I didn't optimize circuits of such depth. Rather, I optimized values of discrete functions directly. Interestingly, I found that the best possible approximation is not significanltly better than the approximation one can get with depth 1 circuits and the same number of qubits.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h1 id="Setup">Setup<a class="anchor-link" href="#Setup"> </a></h1>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Lognormal-distribution-and-L2-error">Lognormal distribution and L2 error<a class="anchor-link" href="#Lognormal-distribution-and-L2-error"> </a></h2>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>The following cells define the lognormal distribution $f(x)$ itself as well as antiderivatives $\int dx f(x)$  and $\int dx f^2(x)$. Andtiderivatives will be useful for computing the L2 error.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
    {% raw %}
    
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">lognormal</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">s</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">0.1</span>
    <span class="n">mu</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">0</span>

    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="mi">1</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sqrt</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">2</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">pi</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">x</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">s</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">exp</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">log</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">mu</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">**</span> <span class="mi">2</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="mi">2</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="n">s</span> <span class="o">**</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">)</span>


<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">lognormal_int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">erf</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">5</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sqrt</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">log</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">))</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="mi">2</span>


<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">lognormal_squared_int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">erf</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">10</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">log</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">1</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="mi">2</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sqrt</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">pi</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="mi">5</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">power</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">e</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">1</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="mi">400</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Uncomment to verify correctness of antiderivatives</span>
<span class="c1"># x = jnp.linspace(0.01, 2, 100)</span>

<span class="c1"># print(jnp.allclose(vmap(lognormal)(x)**2, vmap(grad(lognormal_squared_int))(x)))</span>

<p>Now we will define a simple class collecting some useful data about piecewise constant functions.</p>

<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">

    <span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">condlist</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="k">return</span> <span class="p">[(</span><span class="n">g_left</span> <span class="o">&lt;</span> <span class="n">x</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">&amp;</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span> <span class="o">&lt;=</span> <span class="n">g_right</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">g_left</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">g_right</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">zip</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">:])]</span>

    <span class="nd">@classmethod</span>            
    <span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">from_probabilities</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">cls</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">probs</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="n">values</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">probs</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">:]</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">[:</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">])</span>
        <span class="k">return</span> <span class="bp">cls</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">values</span><span class="p">)</span>      
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
    {% endraw %}

<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>Here is the function that computes the L2 error between a given discrete function and the lognormal distribution. I used the equation</p>
<p>{% raw %}
$$L2=\int_a^b (v-p(x))^2=D^{-1}p(x)^2\Big|^a_b-2 v D^{-1} p(x)\Big|^a_b+v^2 (b-a)$$
{% endraw %}</p>
<p>This is an error of approximating function $p(x)$ by a constant $v$ on an interval $(a,b)$. That this function is correct is confirmed by comparison with other independent methods which I presented above. This (a bit fancy) form is useful for speed in my numerical optimization.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
    {% raw %}
    
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">

<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">l2_error_contributions</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">discrete_function</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">left</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">right</span><span class="p">):</span>
    
    <span class="n">grid</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">discrete_function</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">grid</span>
    <span class="n">values</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">discrete_function</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">values</span>
    
    <span class="c1"># inner contributions</span>
    <span class="n">f_squared_contrib</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">vmap</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">lognormal_squared_int</span><span class="p">)(</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">:])</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">vmap</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">lognormal_squared_int</span><span class="p">)(</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">[:</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">])</span>
    <span class="n">f_contrib</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">vmap</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">lognormal_int</span><span class="p">)(</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">:])</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">vmap</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">lognormal_int</span><span class="p">)(</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">[:</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">])</span>
    <span class="n">const_contrib</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">values</span> <span class="o">**</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">:]</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">[:</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">])</span>

    <span class="c1"># outer contributions</span>
    <span class="n">outer_contrib_left</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">lognormal_squared_int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">])</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">lognormal_squared_int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">left</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">outer_contrib_right</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">lognormal_squared_int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">right</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">lognormal_squared_int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">])</span>

    <span class="c1"># total</span>
    <span class="n">total_contribs</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">f_squared_contrib</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="mi">2</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">f_contrib</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">values</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">const_contrib</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">outer_contrib_left</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">outer_contrib_right</span>

    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">total_contribs</span>


<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">l2_error</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">discrete_function</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">left</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">right</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">inf</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sqrt</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">l2_error_contributions</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">discrete_function</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">left</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">right</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sum</span><span class="p">())</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

<h2 id="Optimization-setup-(irrelevant)">Optimization setup (irrelevant)<a class="anchor-link" href="#Optimization-setup-(irrelevant)"> </a></h2>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>I use <code>JAX</code> for numerical optimization. It is very flexible and efficient, by lacks some of the high level API present in other libraries. The code below is only to setup numerical minimization with <code>JAX</code>, it has no relation to the problem. It is included here only in order to make the notebook self-contained.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
    {% raw %}
    
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">

<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">update_step</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">loss_and_grad</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">opt</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">opt_state</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">params</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">loss</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">grads</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">loss_and_grad</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">params</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">updates</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">opt_state</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">opt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">update</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">grads</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">opt_state</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">params</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">optax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">apply_updates</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">params</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">updates</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">params</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">loss</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">opt_state</span>


<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">glue_params</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">params</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">concatenate</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">params</span><span class="p">)</span>


<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">unglue_params</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">glued_params</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">slice_indices</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">glued_params</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">i0</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="n">i1</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">i0</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">i1</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">zip</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">slice_indices</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">slice_indices</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">:])]</span>


<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">mynimize</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">loss</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">initial_params</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">opt_options</span><span class="p">):</span>
    
    <span class="c1"># Initialize optimizer and parameter splits.</span>
    <span class="n">loss_and_grad</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">value_and_grad</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">loss</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">opt</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">opt_options</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">optimizer</span><span class="p">()</span>
    <span class="n">opt_state</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">opt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">init</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">initial_params</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">sizes</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">ip</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">ip</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">initial_params</span><span class="p">]</span>
    <span class="n">slice_indices</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="nb">sum</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">sizes</span><span class="p">[:</span><span class="n">i</span><span class="p">])</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">sizes</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)]</span>

    <span class="c1"># Single learning iteration compatible with lax fori loop.</span>
    <span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">iteration_with_history</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">i</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">carry</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="n">glued_params_history</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">loss_history</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">opt_state</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">carry</span>
        <span class="n">glued_params</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">glued_params_history</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">i</span><span class="p">]</span>
        
        <span class="n">params</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">unglue_params</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">glued_params</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">slice_indices</span><span class="p">)</span>
        
        <span class="n">params</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">initial_params</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">_make</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">params</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">params</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">loss</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">opt_state</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">update_step</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">loss_and_grad</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">opt</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">opt_state</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">params</span><span class="p">)</span>
        
        <span class="n">glued_params</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">glue_params</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">params</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">glued_params_history</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">glued_params_history</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">at</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">i</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">glued_params</span><span class="p">)</span>
        
        <span class="n">loss_history</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">loss_history</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">at</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">i</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">loss</span><span class="p">)</span>
        
        <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">glued_params_history</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">loss_history</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">opt_state</span>

    <span class="c1"># Initialize arrays holding whole histories for parameters and values.</span>
    <span class="n">glued_initial_params</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">glue_params</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">initial_params</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">glued_params_history</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">zeros</span><span class="p">((</span><span class="n">opt_options</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">num_iterations</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">glued_initial_params</span><span class="p">)))</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">at</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">glued_initial_params</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">loss_history</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">zeros</span><span class="p">((</span><span class="n">opt_options</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">num_iterations</span><span class="p">,))</span>

    <span class="c1"># Optimize iteratively within fori loop.</span>
    <span class="n">glued_params_history</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">loss_history</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">_</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">lax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">fori_loop</span><span class="p">(</span>
        <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span>
        <span class="n">opt_options</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">num_iterations</span><span class="p">,</span>
        <span class="n">iteration_with_history</span><span class="p">,</span>
        <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">glued_params_history</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">loss_history</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">opt_state</span><span class="p">))</span>
    
    <span class="c1"># Bring parameters to the original representation.</span>
    <span class="n">params_history</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">vmap</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="k">lambda</span> <span class="n">gp</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">unglue_params</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">gp</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">slice_indices</span><span class="p">))(</span><span class="n">glued_params_history</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">reordered_params_history</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">initial_params</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">_make</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="n">params_history</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">num_param</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="n">num_iteration</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">num_param</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">initial_params</span><span class="p">))])</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">num_iteration</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">opt_options</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">num_iterations</span><span class="p">)]</span>

    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">reordered_params_history</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">loss_history</span>


<span class="nd">@dataclass</span>
<span class="k">class</span> <span class="nc">OptOptions</span><span class="p">:</span>
    <span class="n">learning_rate</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="nb">float</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">0.01</span>
    <span class="n">num_iterations</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="nb">int</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">2000</span>
    <span class="n">random_seed</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="nb">int</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">0</span>

    <span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">optimizer</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">optax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">adam</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">learning_rate</span><span class="p">)</span>
    
<span class="k">class</span> <span class="nc">OptResult</span><span class="p">:</span>
    <span class="k">def</span> <span class="fm">__init__</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">raw_result</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">loss_func</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">opt_options</span><span class="p">):</span>

        <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">loss_func</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">loss_func</span>
        <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">opt_options</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">opt_options</span>
        <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">params_history</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">raw_result</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span>
        <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">loss_history</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">raw_result</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]</span>
        
        <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">_best_i</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">argmin</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">loss_history</span><span class="p">)</span>
        
        <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">best_params</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">params_history</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">_best_i</span><span class="p">]</span>
        <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">best_loss</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">loss_history</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">_best_i</span><span class="p">]</span>

    <span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">_i_or_best_i</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">i</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="ow">is</span> <span class="kc">None</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="k">return</span> <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">_best_i</span>
        <span class="k">else</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">i</span>

    <span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">plot_loss_history</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">loss_history</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">yscale</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;log&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
        
    <span class="k">def</span> <span class="fm">__repr__</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="k">return</span> <span class="sa">f</span><span class="s1">&#39;OptResult: best_loss </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">best_loss</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1">.&#39;</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>

<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h1 id="Warm-up:-fitting-discrete-functions-directly">Warm-up: fitting discrete functions directly<a class="anchor-link" href="#Warm-up:-fitting-discrete-functions-directly"> </a></h1>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>I found it very istructive to see what accuracy can be achieved if one can fully control values of the discrete function. Empirically, the best strtategy seems to</p>
<ul>
<li>First optimize values of the discrete function with fixed discretization.</li>
<li>Continue by optimizing values and adjusting discretization intervals jointly.</li>
</ul>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Fitting-values-only">Fitting values only<a class="anchor-link" href="#Fitting-values-only"> </a></h2>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>Here is the function that does the first part of the job.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
    {% raw %}
    
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">

<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">V</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">namedtuple</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;Values&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;values&#39;</span><span class="p">])</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">fit_values</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">discrete_function</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">opt_options</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">OptOptions</span><span class="p">()):</span>
    
    <span class="n">grid</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">discrete_function</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">grid</span>
    <span class="n">initial_values</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">discrete_function</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">values</span>
    
    <span class="nd">@jit</span>
    <span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">loss</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">v</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="n">values</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">v</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">values</span>
        <span class="n">df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">DiscreteFunction</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">values</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">l2_error</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">)</span>
    
    <span class="n">initial_params</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">V</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">initial_values</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">results</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">mynimize</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">loss</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">initial_params</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">opt_options</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">OptResult</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">results</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">loss</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">opt_options</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
    {% endraw %}

<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>Here is the best this method can do with 10 qubits starting from random initial values between 0 and 1 (you can change the number of qubits if you wish). The histogram shows density of the grid points. At this point they are distributed uniformly.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
    {% raw %}
    
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">

<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">num_qubits</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">10</span>

<span class="n">grid</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">linspace</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mf">0.5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">1.5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="n">num_qubits</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">initial_values</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">random</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">uniform</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">random</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">PRNGKey</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="n">num_qubits</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="p">))</span>
<span class="n">df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">DiscreteFunction</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">initial_values</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">res</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">fit_values</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">res</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">df_fit</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">DiscreteFunction</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">res</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">best_params</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">values</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">res_values_only</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">res</span>
<span class="n">df_fit_values_only</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df_fit</span>

<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">subplot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">res</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot_loss_history</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">title</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;loss history&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">subplot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">df_fit</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">()</span>

<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">hist</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">array</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df_fit</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">bins</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df_fit</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">density</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">True</span><span class="p">);</span>
</pre></div>

<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Fitting-values-and-grid">Fitting values and grid<a class="anchor-link" href="#Fitting-values-and-grid"> </a></h2>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>Now we introduce the second optimization procedure, which also adjusts discretization intervals.</p>
<p>One technical subtlety here is that the grid points should never go past each other. In order to prevent that I use auxilary variables, which are square roots of the distances between neighboring grid points, <code>grid_roots</code>. Even if some <code>grid_root</code> becomes negative the distance between the grid points <code>grid_root**2</code> stays positive.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
    {% raw %}
    
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">

<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">VG</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">namedtuple</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;ValuesGrid&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;values&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">&#39;grid_roots&#39;</span><span class="p">])</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">grid_to_roots</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">all_points</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">concatenate</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">array</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]),</span> <span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">])</span> <span class="c1"># Append &#39;0&#39; to the left.</span>
    <span class="n">cells</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">all_points</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">:]</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">all_points</span><span class="p">[:</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sqrt</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">cells</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">roots_to_grid</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">roots</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="sd">&quot;&quot;&quot; A bit of complicated syntaxis to restore grid from roots in a jax-compatible way.&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
    <span class="n">cells</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">roots</span> <span class="o">**</span> <span class="mi">2</span>
    <span class="n">masks</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">tri</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">roots</span><span class="p">))</span>
    <span class="n">pre_grid</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">vmap</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="k">lambda</span> <span class="n">x</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">cells</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">x</span><span class="p">)(</span><span class="n">masks</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">pre_grid</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sum</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">axis</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>


<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">fit_values_and_grid</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">discrete_function</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">opt_options</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">OptOptions</span><span class="p">()):</span>

    <span class="n">initial_grid_roots</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">grid_to_roots</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">discrete_function</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">initial_values</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">discrete_function</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">values</span>
    
    <span class="nd">@jit</span>
    <span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">loss</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">vg</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="n">grid</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">roots_to_grid</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">vg</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">grid_roots</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">DiscreteFunction</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">vg</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">values</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">l2_error</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">)</span>
    
    <span class="n">initial_params</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">VG</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">initial_values</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">initial_grid_roots</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">results</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">mynimize</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">loss</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">initial_params</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">opt_options</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">OptResult</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">results</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">loss</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">opt_options</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
    {% endraw %}

<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>Here is the best fit to the lognormal distribution this procedure is able to find. Note that grid points are no longer distributed uniformly but clamp near the regions with the highest slope, as they should (this is in fact better visible at smaller qubit count). Note that here we initialized the optimization with values found at the previous stage. If we were to initialize them randomly, the result would be much worse. Note also a smaller learning rate at this stage.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
    {% raw %}
    
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">

<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">num_qubits</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">10</span>

<span class="n">initial_grid</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df_fit_values_only</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">grid</span>
<span class="n">initial_values</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df_fit_values_only</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">values</span>

<span class="n">df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">DiscreteFunction</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">initial_grid</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">initial_values</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">opt_options</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">OptOptions</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">learning_rate</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">1e-4</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">num_iterations</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">5000</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">res</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">fit_values_and_grid</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">opt_options</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">res</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">best_values</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">res</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">best_params</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">values</span>
<span class="n">best_grid</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">roots_to_grid</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">res</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">best_params</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">grid_roots</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">df_fit</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">DiscreteFunction</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">best_grid</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">best_values</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">subplot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">res</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot_loss_history</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">title</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;loss history&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">subplot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">df_fit</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">title</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;discretization&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">hist</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">array</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df_fit</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">bins</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df_fit</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">density</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">True</span><span class="p">);</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="output_wrapper">
<div class="output">

<div class="output_subarea output_stream output_stdout output_text">

<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h1 id="Fitting-quantum-circuit">Fitting quantum circuit<a class="anchor-link" href="#Fitting-quantum-circuit"> </a></h1>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="MyCircuit-class">MyCircuit class<a class="anchor-link" href="#MyCircuit-class"> </a></h2>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>First I will define a very simple <code>MyCircuit</code> class that bundles <code>qiskit</code> representation with <code>jax</code>-compatible unitary. For the purposes of this notebook, we only need to place one gate on each qubit.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
    {% raw %}
    
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">

<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">U_gate</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">a</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">theta</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">phi</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">lmbda</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">a</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">array</span><span class="p">([[</span><span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">cos</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">theta</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">exp</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="n">j</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="n">lmbda</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sin</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">theta</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">)],</span>

<span class="k">class</span> <span class="nc">MyCircuit</span><span class="p">:</span>
    <span class="k">def</span> <span class="fm">__init__</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">num_qubits</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">num_qubits</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">num_qubits</span>
    
    <span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">qiskit_circuit</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">angles</span><span class="p">):</span>

        <span class="n">qc</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">QuantumCircuit</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">num_qubits</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">angles</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">array</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">angles</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1"># Qiskit does not accept JAX arrays.</span>
        <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">i</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">theta</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">phi</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">lmbda</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">enumerate</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">angles</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">reshape</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">num_qubits</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">)):</span>
            <span class="n">qc</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">u</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">theta</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">phi</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">lmbda</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">i</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">unitary</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">angles</span><span class="p">):</span>

        <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">reduce</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">kron</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">gates</span><span class="p">)</span>
    
    <span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">_verify</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">angles</span><span class="p">):</span>

<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Defining-loss-associated-with-a-unitary">Defining loss associated with a unitary<a class="anchor-link" href="#Defining-loss-associated-with-a-unitary"> </a></h2>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>Quantum circuit transforms the input state. Amplitudes of the output state encode the values of the discrete function that we use to fit the lognormal distribution. Here we construct a function that takes a quantum circuit and returns the L2 error of the corresponding approximation.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
    {% raw %}
    
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">

<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">loss_from_unitary</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">u</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">probs</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">probabilities_from_unitary</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">u</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">DiscreteFunction</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">from_probabilities</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">probs</span><span class="p">)</span>
    
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">l2_error</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">probabilities_from_unitary</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">u</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">all_zero_state</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">zeros</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">u</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">shape</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">])</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">at</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">amplitudes</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">amplitudes_from_state</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">u</span> <span class="o">@</span> <span class="n">all_zero_state</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">probabilities</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">abs</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">amplitudes</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="mi">2</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">probabilities</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">amplitudes_from_state</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">state</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">vmap</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="k">lambda</span> <span class="n">basis_state</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">state</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">basis_state</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sum</span><span class="p">())(</span><span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">identity</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">state</span><span class="p">)))</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
    {% endraw %}

<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Fitting-angles-only">Fitting angles only<a class="anchor-link" href="#Fitting-angles-only"> </a></h2>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>Now we are ready to optimize angles in the circuit for the best fit to the target distribution. Discretization is held fixed at this stage.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
    {% raw %}
    
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">

<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">A</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">namedtuple</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;Angles&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;angles&#39;</span><span class="p">])</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">fit_angles</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">num_qubits</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">opt_options</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">OptOptions</span><span class="p">()):</span>
    <span class="k">assert</span> <span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="n">num_qubits</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="sa">f</span><span class="s1">&#39;Grid length </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1"> does not match number of qubits </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">num_qubits</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1">.&#39;</span>
    <span class="n">circuit</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">MyCircuit</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">num_qubits</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="nd">@jit</span>
    <span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">loss</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">a</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="n">u</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">circuit</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">unitary</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">a</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">angles</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">loss_from_unitary</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">u</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="n">initial_angles</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">random</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">uniform</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">random</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">PRNGKey</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">opt_options</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">random_seed</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="n">num_qubits</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">minval</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">maxval</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">pi</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">initial_params</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">A</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">initial_angles</span><span class="p">)</span>
    
    <span class="n">results</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">mynimize</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">loss</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">initial_params</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">opt_options</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">OptResult</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">results</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">loss</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">opt_options</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
    {% endraw %}

</div>

</div>

</div>
    {% endraw %}

<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>The highly asymmetric shape of the fitting function here is typical and continutes to higher qubits. At the first glance, there seems to be little hope of making the construction work. However, as we see right now, adjusting the discretization ranges cuts the deal.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Fitting-angles-and-grid">Fitting angles and grid<a class="anchor-link" href="#Fitting-angles-and-grid"> </a></h2>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>Here is the procedure that fits angles and grid together. We bundle it with the previous step into a single simple function <code>fit_circuit</code> that does all the work.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
    {% raw %}
    
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">

<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">AG</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">namedtuple</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;AnglesGrid&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;angles&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">&#39;grid_roots&#39;</span><span class="p">])</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">fit_angles_and_grid</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">initial_angles</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">initial_grid</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">opt_options</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">OptOptions</span><span class="p">()):</span>
    <span class="n">num_qubits</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">initial_angles</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="k">assert</span> <span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">initial_grid</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="n">num_qubits</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="sa">f</span><span class="s1">&#39;Grid length </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1"> does not match number of qubits </span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">num_qubits</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s1">.&#39;</span>
    <span class="n">circuit</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">MyCircuit</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">num_qubits</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="nd">@jit</span>
    <span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">loss</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">ag</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="n">u</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">circuit</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">unitary</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">ag</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">angles</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">grid</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">roots_to_grid</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">ag</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">grid_roots</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">loss_from_unitary</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">u</span><span class="p">)</span>
    
    <span class="n">initial_grid_roots</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">grid_to_roots</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">initial_grid</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">initial_params</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">AG</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">initial_angles</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">initial_grid_roots</span><span class="p">)</span>
    
    <span class="n">results</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">mynimize</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">loss</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">initial_params</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">opt_options</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">OptResult</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">results</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">loss</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">opt_options</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">fit_circuit</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">num_qubits</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;Initial optimization of angles:&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">grid</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">jnp</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">linspace</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mf">0.6</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">1.5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="n">num_qubits</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">res</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">fit_angles</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">num_qubits</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">res</span><span class="p">)</span>
    
    <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;</span><span class="se">\n</span><span class="s1">Optimization of angles and grid:&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">circuit</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">MyCircuit</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">num_qubits</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="n">initial_angles</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">res</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">best_params</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">angles</span>
    <span class="n">initial_grid</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">grid</span>

    <span class="n">opt_options</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">OptOptions</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">learning_rate</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">1e-4</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">num_iterations</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">10000</span><span class="p">)</span>
    
    <span class="n">res</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">fit_angles_and_grid</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">initial_angles</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">initial_grid</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">opt_options</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">res</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="n">best_probs</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">probabilities_from_unitary</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">circuit</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">unitary</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">res</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">best_params</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">angles</span><span class="p">))</span>
    <span class="n">best_grid</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">roots_to_grid</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">res</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">best_params</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">grid_roots</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="n">df_fit</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">DiscreteFunction</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">from_probabilities</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">best_grid</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">best_probs</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">subplot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">res</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot_loss_history</span><span class="p">()</span>
    <span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">title</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;loss history&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">subplot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">df_fit</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">()</span>
    <span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">hist</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">array</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df_fit</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">bins</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df_fit</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">density</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">True</span><span class="p">);</span>
    <span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">title</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;discretization&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
    
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">circuit</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">qiskit_circuit</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">res</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">best_params</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">angles</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">qasm</span><span class="p">(),</span> <span class="n">best_grid</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
    {% endraw %}

<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
